  include it as a parameter in a URL that is posted publicly or e-mailed directly to victims.

  - CVE-2020-35590: When the plugin is configured to accept an arbitrary header for the client source
  IP address, a malicious user is not limited to perform a brute force attack, because the client IP
  header accepts any arbitrary string. When randomizing the header input, the login count does not
  ever reach the maximum allowed retries.");

